        </div>
        <div class="border-[3px] border-red-500 bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Does Wix's app marketplace justify the higher cost?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Wix's app marketplace can justify the higher cost IF you genuinely need multiple apps. Wix offers 5000+ apps for: booking systems, email marketing, CRM, live chat, membership areas, analytics, automation tools. Each app typically costs $10-30/month. The value proposition: if you need 3+ apps, Wix's all-in-one integration saves time and technical complexity. However, many users fall into the 'feature trap' - adding apps they don't need because they're available. Zyro's constraints force focus on essentials. The brutal truth: most websites need 3-5 features maximum. If you genuinely need 7+ integrated features, Wix pays for itself. If you need basic functionality, Zyro saves significant money.</p>
